block.p: Sheelah Anne Morrissey, a daughter of Elizabeth T. Morrissey and Kevin E. Morrissey of Manhasset, N.Y., was married there yesterday to Joseph Gerard Quinn, a son of Sharon M. Quinn and William J. Quinn of Palm Beach, Fla. The Rev. Matthew A. Quinn performed the ceremony at St. Mary's Roman Catholic Church.

Mrs. Quinn, who will continue to use her maiden name professionally, is a senior account executive in the Norwalk, Conn., sales office of R. R. Donnelley & Sons, the printing company. She graduated from Iona College. Her father owns an insurance agency in Woodside, Queens.

Sheelah Anne Morrissey, a daughter of Elizabeth T. Morrissey and Kevin E. Morrissey of Manhasset, N.Y., was married there yesterday to Joseph Gerard Quinn, a son of Sharon M. Quinn and William J. Quinn of Palm Beach, Fla. The Rev. Matthew A. Quinn performed the ceremony at St. Mary's Roman Catholic Church.

Mrs. Quinn, who will continue to use her maiden name professionally, is a senior account executive in the Norwalk, Conn., sales office of R. R. Donnelley & Sons, the printing company. She graduated from Iona College. Her father owns an insurance agency in Woodside, Queens.

Mr. Quinn is the director of finance for the J. Crew Group, the clothing retailer and catalog company in Manhattan. He graduated from Albion College. His mother is a home health-care nurse in Palm Beach. His father retired as the director of quality control for the Chrysler Corporation in Detroit.
